    <div class="about-agent">
      <h1 class="headingss"><span>Whats A Real Estate Agent Do?</span></h1>
      <div class="agents-what-do">
        <img src="/images/agents/7.jpg" alt="" class="image">
        <p>Real estate agents are knowledgeable about their local laws on the buying and selling of property. The
          geographical area that an agent works in is their area of expertise. They know trends within the local
          property market as well as what competitive prices are for the various properties their clients want to buy or
          sell.
          <br> <br>
          A real estate agent acts as the middleman, or broker, between two parties seeking to buy or sell a property.
          Real estate agents have the skill and expertise to either market the property and sell for the best possible
          price and conditions, or to look for property that suits a client's needs and buy it at the best price
          possible with the most favourable terms.
          <br><br>
          Negotiation is a key part of the real estate agent's work, as they act as the intermediary between buyer and
          seller and will often negotiate on their client's behalf. Real estate agents will charge a percentage of the
          final sale price as their fee.
        </p>
